{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260902,"nonce":"ipC+so9w1O3dgnzPYgf1/R+ePRQ=","title":"Two-link arm with 6-muscle activation dynamics training pipeline","message":"Stage 7 in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed). High-cost stage; should only begin once point-mass stages 4–6 results are in. Depends on feedbax AnalyticalMusculoskeletalPlant stability.\n\n**Question.** Does adding biomechanical coupling (antagonist muscles, force-length, force-velocity, activation dynamics, signal-dependent noise) restore the \"robust = faster\" velocity signature, even with a full GRU controller? The Riccati framework no longer applies cleanly at this plant, so the test is purely empirical.\n\n**Method.** Switch the plant from feedbax linearize_pointmass to feedbax AnalyticalMusculoskeletalPlant with default_6muscle_2link_topology. Retrain GRUs under the matched ε adversary (020a65b). Compare Δv before and after the plant swap.\n\n**Milestone zero (mandatory first step).** Train a non-adversarial GRU baseline on the muscle plant to confirm the pipeline is numerically stable before introducing any adversary. Do not skip this step — the muscle plant is less battle-tested.\n\n**Metrics.** Endpoint Δv, antagonist co-activation index, signal-dependent noise level, total muscle activation cost, robustness to held-out perturbation classes (curl, viscous, divergent). Apply the decoupling decomposition (8fcb6c7) to the resulting controller to see how the u_ff / K_local partition shifts in muscle space.\n\n**Falsification.** If Δv stays ≈ 0 or goes negative in muscle space, human velocity inflation is not explained by biomechanical coupling alone — task/strategy explanations are needed. If Δv goes positive, the C\u0026S signature is largely biomechanical and the point-mass null result does not generalise.\n\n**Cross-refs.** Plan §3 stage 7. Feedbax AnalyticalMusculoskeletalPlant. Decoupling decomposition 8fcb6c7. Training-methods coord c99ad9d.","files":null}]}